# Toast Notifications

Use `useKubevirtToast` from `@kubevirt-utils/hooks/useKubevirtToast` for all toast notifications. Never import `useToast` from `@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk` directly — the wrapper provides backward compatibility with Console <= 4.22 where `useToast` does not exist.

## API

```typescript
import useKubevirtToast from '@kubevirt-utils/hooks/useKubevirtToast';

const { addSuccessToast, addDangerToast, addInfoToast, addWarningToast, addToast, removeToast } =
  useKubevirtToast();
```

### Variant Helpers

Each helper takes an options object (same as `ToastOptions` minus `variant`, with `content` optional) and returns the toast ID (`string`). Only `title` is required.

| Helper | Default behavior |
|--------|-----------------|
| `addSuccessToast` | dismissible, auto-dismiss after 8s |
| `addInfoToast` | dismissible, auto-dismiss after 8s |
| `addWarningToast` | dismissible, persists until closed |
| `addDangerToast` | dismissible, persists until closed |

### Raw `addToast`

For full control, use `addToast(options)` with the SDK's `ToastOptions` type directly (requires `variant`).

### `removeToast`

Call `removeToast(id)` with the toast ID returned by any `add*Toast` call.

## Examples

```typescript
// Title only
addSuccessToast({ title: t('VM created successfully') });

// Title + body content
addDangerToast({ content: errorMessage, title: t('Failed to delete VM') });

// With extra options
addInfoToast({ content: t('You can navigate away.'), timeout: 15000, title: t('Upload started') });

// Store ID for later removal
const id = addWarningToast({ title: t('Migration in progress') });
// ... later
removeToast(id);
```
